{
  "stem": "3848.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were killed right there, the first day, the day that he left for the Russian Army.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, he wanted to take revenge, and in Donskoe he volunteered to the Russian Army, and he was sent to fight.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He was fighting with the Russian Army in the Carpathian mountains in Czechoslovakia, I found out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "After the war ended, he was still in the mountains.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He didn't know the war ended, and that's where he is.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But I'm going to tell you how we found-- he found me again after that, because I didn't know where he was anymore.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He left.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "When I came to Kiev, we were traveling on a transport with a lot of Polish people towards Poland.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Well, I didn't know which stations they were going to go through, but one morning they stopped.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I walked out of the train, and I looked out, and I saw a church.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The church looked familiar to me, because it was a Polish church-- a kosciol-- and from the station, I looked at it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I said to my friends, I said, you know, it looks like we are already in Poland-- in the former Poland-- because I can recognize the churches.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "This happened to be my own city, Rowne, which I didn't recognize.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The whole city was completely bombarded.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The only thing they left-- was left in the city was the church, the kosciol-- the Polish kosciol.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "There was a big Jewish synagogue was left standing because it looked like a church.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "There was the [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Szabo ?] the Russian Orthodox Church, was also left, which is standing even today.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The rest of the city was completely destroyed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Only a few buildings were left.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
